In criminal law. A
combination or confederacy between two or
more persons formed for the purpose of committing, by their joint efforts, some unlawful or criminal act, or some act which is innocent in itself, but becomes unlawful when
done by the concerted action of the conspirators, or for the purpose of using criminal or
unlawful means to the commission of an act
not in itself unlawful. Pettibone v. U. S.,
